alas, poor ape,how thou sweatest!
come, let me wipe thy face;come on, you whoreson chops: ah, rogue!
i'faith, Ilove thee: thou art as valorous as Hector of Troy,worth five of Agamemnon, and ten times better thanthe Nine Worthies: ah, villain!
